subSubSection.paragraph:
Metathorax
: dorsally with a narrow band of hs + a few lp extending across full width of segment, representing metatergal setae (mts) and dorsospiracular setae (dss). Metathoracic spiracle (sp 
3
): width of peritreme about 11–13 µm, with 1 associated lp. Metasternum (stn 
3
) with a pair of hs + a pair of lp anteriorly.
